# 3. Critical Decisions & Reasoning History

**Freshness: ✅ High.**

- FastAPI is the only system of record; Streamlit never opens the database or receives provider
  credentials.
- Custom deterministic metrics were chosen for a complete offline core; optional judge/plugin work
  cannot replace or destabilize that core.
- Preflight and run creation share one transaction and persist the accepted snapshot, preventing a
  time-of-check/time-of-use matrix drift.
- Provider output/usage/request ID/cost is committed before scoring so evaluator failure cannot erase
  billable evidence.
- Only HTTP 429 is automatically retried; ambiguous 5xx/timeouts are not repeated.
- Reference answers are evaluator-only; templates accept only `{input}` and `{context}`.
- SQLite is the default complete database path; PostgreSQL is supported but does not imply
  distributed-worker safety.
- Operational metrics remain separate from quality; every denominator and unavailable value stays
  explicit.
- The dashboard uses root-first navigation for deterministic cold-start behavior.

