# 8. Risks, Technical Debt & Strict Preservation Rules

**Freshness: ✅ High.**

- Lexical metrics can be gamed and are not factual truth; preserve explicit limitations and
  applicability.
- SQLite and the in-process executor are single-node primitives.
- Local files/exports may contain sensitive prompts and outputs.
- **Do not touch without explicit instruction:**
  - Do not allow `{expected_output}` or any reference alias in candidate prompts.
  - Do not put credentials/base URLs in model profiles, requests, exports, UI fields, fixtures, or
    logs.
  - Do not auto-retry ambiguous provider failures or fall back between API modes.
  - Do not report unknown pricing as zero or demo latency/usage as live.
  - Do not combine latency/cost into aggregate quality.
  - Do not mutate run/case/prompt/model/preflight snapshots after creation.
  - Do not add API workers while SQLite/local claiming is in use.
  - Do not use Cypress for E2E; this Python/Streamlit app uses Playwright.
  - Do not remove migration 0002 retry safety or its populated-FK tests.
  - Do not flatten local Compose evidence into hosted or production proof.

